<item>
            <title>[DERBY-1762] Setting the derby.locks.waitTimeout as a system property using System.setProperty does not affect booted databases</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-1762</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Tuning guide for derby.locks.waitTimeout states it is a dynamic property, but when set as a system property using System.setProperty it does not change the timeout for any databases already booted. It might change it for databases that are booted after the change, I didn&apos;t test that.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If the property is set as a database property then it is dynamic, taking effect immediately.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Guess it affects all versions.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
